**Alternatively**, we can use `enum` and get rid of the child classes as they do not add any properties/functionalities to the `Employee` class. In that case 

**Employee.java**
```java
public class Employee {
    public enum Status {
        MANAGER,
        WORKER
    }

    private int employeeID;
    private double salary;

    private Status status;

    //Constructor
    public Employee(int ID, double esalary, Status stat) {
        employeeID = ID;
        salary = esalary;
        status = stat;
    }

    //Getter ID
    public int getID() {
        return employeeID;
    }

    //Setter ID
    public void setID(int ID) {
        employeeID = ID;
    }

    //Getter Salary
    public double getSalary() {
        return salary;
    }

    //Setter Salary
    public void setSalary(double esalary) {
        salary = esalary;
    }

    public Status getStatus() {
        return status;
    }

    public void setStatus(Status status) {
        this.status = status;
    }
}
```
And your `main` method would become
```java
